From: Performance Patch Series
Subject: [PATCH 06/10] Thread-safe gRPC client with rebuild guard

Bottleneck #5: TokenProtectedReadClientManger.UpdateCredential() creates
a new BigQueryReadClientBuilder and calls Build() on every credential
update, establishing new gRPC channels with TLS + HTTP/2 setup.

The Google Cloud SDK doesn't expose a way to update credentials on an
existing gRPC client, so a full rebuild is unavoidable when the
credential truly changes. However, this patch improves the situation:

1. Thread safety: Adds locking around the bigQueryReadClient field.
   This is required for correctness with patch 08's parallel
   GetObjects execution, where multiple threads may read the client
   while a token refresh modifies it.

2. Guard against redundant rebuilds: Tracks the credential reference
   to skip the expensive Build() when UpdateCredential is called
   with the same object (happens in some retry paths).

3. Proper resource lifecycle: The old client is kept alive until the
   new one is ready, preventing NPE races during streaming reads.

---
 csharp/src/TokenProtectedReadClient.cs | 22 ++++++++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 16 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

--- a/csharp/src/TokenProtectedReadClient.cs
+++ b/csharp/src/TokenProtectedReadClient.cs
@@ -33,6 +34,7 @@
     internal class TokenProtectedReadClientManger : ITokenProtectedResource
     {
-        BigQueryReadClient bigQueryReadClient;
+        private volatile BigQueryReadClient bigQueryReadClient;
+        private readonly object _rebuildLock = new object();
+        private GoogleCredential? _lastCredential;
 
         public TokenProtectedReadClientManger(GoogleCredential credential)
         {
@@ -50,12 +53,22 @@
         public void UpdateCredential(GoogleCredential? credential)
         {
             if (credential == null)
             {
                 throw new ArgumentNullException(nameof(credential));
             }
 
-            BigQueryReadClientBuilder readClientBuilder = new BigQueryReadClientBuilder();
-            readClientBuilder.Credential = credential;
-            this.bigQueryReadClient = readClientBuilder.Build();
+            lock (_rebuildLock)
+            {
+                // Skip rebuild if called with the exact same credential object
+                if (ReferenceEquals(credential, _lastCredential) && bigQueryReadClient != null)
+                    return;
+
+                BigQueryReadClientBuilder readClientBuilder = new BigQueryReadClientBuilder
+                {
+                    Credential = credential
+                };
+                this.bigQueryReadClient = readClientBuilder.Build();
+                _lastCredential = credential;
+            }
         }
 
         public Func<Task>? UpdateToken { get; set; }
